cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is about robotic grasping, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses convolutional neural networks (cs.CV) to predict the robustness of a grasp and a distribution of post-grasp object displacements. The use of neural networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the method is designed for industrial applications, which often involve control systems (cs.SY).
